In the span of a few weeks, I’ve gone from someone who hates eating leftovers to someone who feels immense gratitude when I have leftovers in my fridge.
For years, I’ve been storing leftovers in widemouthed Mason jars with easy-to-screw-on plastic lids, as they are cheap, plentiful, and aesthetically pleasing.
Oxygen is the enemy when it comes to leftovers, as it makes food wilt and go bad far more quickly.
You’ll have pumped just about all the air you can out of your jar when the pump gets hard to pull up.